# GitHub issue tracking (hardening sprint)

Active sprint epic: **#16** — [Two-week hardening sprint](https://github.com/juanroddotdev/resume-rocket/issues/16)

Child issues:

| Issue | Scope |
|-------|--------|
| #10 | Phase A VMS template mapping |
| #11 | JSONB normalization |
| #12 | Parse outcome visibility |
| #13 | `/api/parse` rate limiting |
| #14 | Automated regression tests |
| #15 | Release checklist |

Source checklists: `docs/PROJECT-REVIEW.md` §7–§8.

## When committing or opening a PR

1. **Identify** which issue(s) the branch addresses (one concern per PR when possible).
2. **PR title/body** must reference them:
   - `Closes #10` when the issue is fully done in that PR
   - `Part of #16` + `Addresses #11` when partial or stacked
3. **Test plan** should mirror the issue's test plan checkboxes from §8.

## Before push / `gh pr create`

- [ ] PR links at least one of #10–#15 (or #16 if meta/docs only)
- [ ] If work completes an issue, PR body includes `Closes #N`
- [ ] Epic #16 milestone checklist updated if multiple children done in one merge

## After merge (or when user asks to ship)

If the merged work **fully satisfies** an issue's tasks and test plan:

```bash
gh issue close N --comment "Completed in PR #___."
```

If only partial, leave open and comment with PR link + remaining checkboxes.

For docs-only PRs that don't close a child issue, reference `Part of #16` only.

## Do not

- Close issues without merged code or docs that match the issue scope
- Bundle unrelated issues in one PR (see `pr-size.mdc`)
